# .trivyignore
# Unfixable OS-level CVEs in python:3.12-slim (debian 13.4)
# No fix available from Debian upstream as of 2025-05-03
# Review date: 2025-08-03

# libcap2 — TOCTOU race in cap_set_file()
# Impact: requires local access + specific file operations — not reachable in containerised Flask app
CVE-2026-4878

# ncurses — buffer overflow
# Impact: ncurses is not used by the application at runtime
CVE-2025-69720

# systemd/udev — IPC code execution
# Impact: systemd is not the init system inside the container; udev is not active
CVE-2026-29111

# --- K8s config suppressions ---

# KSV014 / KSV-0014: readOnlyRootFilesystem for Postgres
# Postgres requires write access to disk for WAL files, temp files, and Unix sockets
# Accepted exception for database containers — cannot be remediated without breaking Postgres
KSV-0014
KSV014

# AVD-KSV-0109: ConfigMap contains secret-shaped keys (AUTH_DB_PASSWORD, TX_DB_PASSWORD)
# These are Postgres container init credentials required for database bootstrap only
# Application runtime secrets are managed by Vault Agent Injector — not this ConfigMap
AVD-KSV-0109